00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,900
Episode 20

27
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:06,100
So pretty.

28
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,600
What's wrong?

29
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:13,600
My grandmother went missing again. She already ran out once last night.

30
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,800
It was your students who brought her back. Where did she go this time?

31
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,400
What do we do then? Should we call the police?

32
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,100
No need.

33
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,400
I'll go to the old house and take a look. She always goes over there.

34
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,400
Wait for me.

35
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,200
Wait!

36
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Boss, this is?

37
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Sorry. Sorry.

38
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,600
Grandmother, you're confused again.

39
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:40,800
Grandmother keeps saying

40
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:43,400
"Nian Nian, Nian Nian". Who's Nian Nian?

41
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:47,400
Niannian is my dad's nickname. His real name is Zeng Younian, right?

42
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,200
I reckon my grandmother thought that these two little students

43
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:53,400
were my dad and my grandpa.

44
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:57,600
Grandma, come, come. Come home with me, okay? Let's go. Let's go home.

45
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,400
Come home.

46
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:01,900
Brother Yuan,

47
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,600
Who is he?

48
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:07,600
- Why does Grandma keep calling me Brother Yuan?
- Sorry, sorry.

49
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:12,000
Grandmother, he's not Brother Yuan.

50
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,400
Take out your picture. Picture. Look at the picture.

51
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,600
- Picture?
- Yes.

52
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:20,000
It's right here.

53
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:32,040
It is Brother Yuan. Exactly.

54
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,500
Grandma, you...

55
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,700
Yuan Brother.

56
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,200
I heard from my mom and dad that

57
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:43,800
my grandma used to be a renowned embroiderer.

58
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:49,200
Later, before my dad was born, my grandpa joined the army and left.

59
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:51,900
After he left, he never came back.

60
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:54,000
A lot of people persuaded her to remarry.

61
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:58,000
But my grandma thinks that my grandpa will come back.

62
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,700
She raised me by herself.

63
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:05,400
The relationship between Grandma and Grandpa must be really good.

64
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,600
Yeah.

65
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:10,800
Before, when my Grandmother didn't become muddled, she'd come here and sit around when she had nothing to do.

66
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:14,600
There, in that backyard.

67
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,600
There was this ginkgo tree.

68
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:22,700
Later, the place was scheduled for demolition and relocation, so they chopped the tree down.

69
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:26,400
From that point on, my Grandmother became more and more confused.

70
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:29,600
She only remembers to come here every day.

71
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:33,800
If the house gets demolished, what will Grandma do?

72
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:37,400
Besides, this old house hasn't been repaired for years.

73
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:39,800
It isn't safe for your grandma to be here so often.

74
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,200
Yeah.

75
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,060
We also have no idea what to do.

76
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:45,800
My grandmother is getting more and more confused.

77
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:49,000
She doesn't remember anything or recognize anyone.

78
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,400
Okay, I won't bother you anymore.

79
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:54,400
Grandma, let's go. Let's go home, okay?

80
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,700
Brother Yuan is here.

81
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:57,800
Time to go home.

82
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,800
Let's go.

83
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:04,600
Daughter-in-law, Son, let's sit over where Brother Yuan is.

84
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,400
Here, come.

85
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:08,800
Brother Yuan, look at what a good match my daughter-in-law and son are.

86
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:12,800
Brother Yuan, look at what a good match my daughter-in-law and son are.

87
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,600
I don't approve of this.

88
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:20,800
Yuan Brother, what did you say?

89
00:05:21,790 --> 00:05:23,680
Nothing.

90
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,800
What a good match.

91
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,200
Okay.

92
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:33,000
Boss, go back to work. Grandma's doing pretty well here. Go back to work.

93
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,200
It's fine. Don't worry.

94
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:38,200
- I'd have to trouble you then.
- All right, all right, you can go back.

95
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,600
Students!

96
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:43,300
Don't stand here anymore. Everyone, do what you need to do.

97
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,000
What were you guys busy doing? Go quickly.

98
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,400
Grandma.

99
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:57,200
- Grandma.
- Have some water.

100
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,800
I won't drink it.

101
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:03,800
Grandma, I got so moved due to your love story that I cried.

102
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:07,600
Teach me how to do that embroidery. I'll be sure to promote it.

103
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,500
I don't teach outsiders.

104
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,600
Drink water.

105
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:17,200
Grandma, take a look at this.

106
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:20,300
You're so disgusting.

107
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:22,300
No laughing.

108
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,800
Kaituo, help convince Grandma for me.

109
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,600
Not going.

110
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:37,000
Do you even have a heart? What's wrong with helping a teacher?

111
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:43,200
Where is Xia Miaomiao? Why did she leave the grandma after bringing her here?

112
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:45,900
You're not allowed to hit Brother Yuan!

113
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:50,800
Grandma, why don't I dance for you?

114
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:53,200
Stay far away from me, seriously.

115
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:56,400
Grandma, I'll dance for you.

116
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:06,800
Ms. Jia, you dance really well.

117
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,200
You can ask me for the favor.

118
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,700
Shut up.

119
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,900
The bed and breakfast owner got us tea.

120
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,340
Thank you.

121
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,420
What are you doing here?

122
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:59,200
Earlier, Boss said that Grandma and Grandpa's

123
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:03,700
ginkgo tree used to be planted here.

124
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,100
Here?

125
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:13,300
I think that grandma is probably the only one who

126
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:17,300
remembers what that ginkgo tree looked like.

127
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:24,200
But Grandma will probably forget about it very soon.

128
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:40,480
Senior. I have an idea.

129
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:45,200
Make a model of grandma's ancestral home?

130
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,200
How did you know?

131
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,600
Brother Yuan, are you thirsty?

132
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,800
No.

133
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,600
Are you hungry?

134
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,400
Hungry?

135
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:07,200
Then I'll clean up the kitchen and we can make food in a bit, okay?

136
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:10,000
Okay! You go.

137
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,200
Grandma, I'll help you.

138
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,800
Lin Kaituo.

139
00:09:33,150 --> 00:09:35,260
Where did you two go together?

140
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:41,020
I have an idea. Listen up.

141
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,400
Speak.

142
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:49,600
Let's make a model of the ancestral home together and restore a ginkgo tree for Grandma.

143
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,100
What do you think?

144
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:55,800
I agree. MiaoMiao, you're in charge of the landscape.

145
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,830
As for you, you'll do the blueprint.

146
00:09:57,830 --> 00:10:00,000
Be my assistant and build the model.

147
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,400
Okay.

148
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,200
Let's start working then.

149
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:06,940
Clean this up.

