If I had known, I wouldn't have said I was hungry. Now great.

151
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:39,700
Grandma won't leave and we still have to cook.

152
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:43,400
Brother Yuan, you talk too much. Go cook.

153
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:48,000
Oh, obedient son. Is this the attitude you use to talk to your dad?

154
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:50,800
- Students!
- Students!

155
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:54,700
Sorry, sorry. You guys still have to cook for yourselves.

156
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:57,800
You sit. I'll buy the stuff soon.

157
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:00,600
The cooking utensils in the old house are too old.

158
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,400
Use the new ones that I just gave you, okay?

159
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,000
It's fine.

160
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,400
Why are you acting nice? it's fine for you, but not for me.

161
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:10,200
- Brother Yuan, let me help you.
- No need.

162
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,600
- Brother Yuan. Brother Yuan.
- No need. No need. Thank you, Grandma. There's no need.

163
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:17,000
Grandma. Let's go back and wash the vegetables, okay? The ones you wash are the cleanest.

164
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,200
I want to help Brother Yuan.

165
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,900
Brother Yuan is waiting to eat the vegetables you've washed, okay?

166
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,200
Try and see if it's salty.

167
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:44,800
What are you doing?

168
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,500
Seeing if it's salty.

169
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,400
Too salty.

170
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,600
Salty? Then what should I do?

171
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:55,300
I'll add some more water.

172
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,000
What are you making?

173
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,800
I'm making egg dumplings.

174
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:19,000
You can even make egg dumplings?

175
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,400
That's so impressive.

176
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:23,300
I've worked more jobs than the amount of salt you've eaten.

177
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,800
All right then, you do it. I'll learn.

178
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,400
Student.

179
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:32,000
Sorry. Can you help me with something?

180
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:36,000
My grandma is making a fuss to see Brother Yuan.

181
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,800
Brother Yuan, did you hear that?

182
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,400
Grandma needs you. Okay?

183
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:46,000
Go!

184
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:51,300
Fine. Then, Brother Yuan is leaving!

185
