190
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:08,020
No.

191
00:14:15,390 --> 00:14:16,970
Miaomiao.

192
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,600
Come out for a sec.

193
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,400
I'm making food, Teacher.

194
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:23,200
Hurry.

195
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,400
But.

196
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:27,600
Go. Teacher is calling for you.

197
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,100
Okay.

198
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:48,500
Look.

199
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Is it pretty?

200
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,600
This is?

201
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:56,600
The owner of the bed and breakfast found me this.

202
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:03,400
Look. If such a beautiful skill isn't handed down, won't it be such a pity?

203
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:07,700
But didn't Grandma say that she only teaches family members?

204
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,800
So I need your help.

205
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,200
Me?

206
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,400
How hard could it be?

207
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,600
If I use this embroidery technique

208
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:17,000
to embroider the ginkgo tree leaves on the model landscape,

209
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,400
it should look even more vivid, right?

210
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:23,800
Just where are you taking me?

211
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:26,400
I still have to pick vegetables with Brother Yuan.

212
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:29,200
Come and take a look and you'll know.

213
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,200
Grandma is here.

214
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:34,000
Daughter-in-law, where's Nian Nian?

215
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,600
Grandmother, this is your daughter-in-law, right?

216
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:38,800
Yeah.

217
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:42,000
She was raised in a good family, right? She's the real thing.

218
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,300
Then, teach her your embroidery skills.

219
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:48,100
Daughter-in-law, do you want to learn?

220
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,410
Yes, I want to learn.

221
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:54,100
Can you teach me how to embroider ginkgo leaves?

222
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:55,800
Of course.

223
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,100
My daughter-in-law is so nice.

224
00:17:00,590 --> 00:17:02,500
You, get out!

225
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,800
Okay.

226
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,300
What's so hard about this?

227
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,400
Everyone can come eat now.

228
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,200
- Come, Grandma. Slowly.
- Okay.

229
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,000
Thank you.

230
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,000
